{"questionId":"28288","questionHtml":"<p>Predict, using the given values, the reaction that would take place at the anode&nbsp;and cathode for the electrolysis of an aqueous solution of ammonium nitrate using&nbsp;graphite electrodes.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/13094c51c9d13c771980c729a1ea219088e205e7.png\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/b644f71c65b8115824121cdff89ec5cef6ea6546.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Anode:</em></p>\n<p>H<sub>2</sub>O (l) → 1/2O<sub>2</sub> (g) + 2H<sup>+</sup> (aq) + 2e<sup>−</sup>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Cathode:</em></p>\n<p>H<sup>+</sup> (aq) + e<sup>−</sup> → 1/2H<sub>2</sub> (g) ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Do <strong>not</strong> accept other equations.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"28288","referenceCode":"22N.2.hl.TZ0.1e","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Predict, using the given values, the reaction that would take place at the anode and cathode for the electrolysis of an aqueous solution of ammonium nitrate using graphite electrod","paper":"2","level":"hl","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes","19.1 Electrochemical cells","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}